          <tr>
            <td valign="top">Difference in proportion TST-positive &amp; QFT-IT-positive was significant in patients with IMID (<italic>P</italic>&#xA0;=&#xA0;0.013) but not in healthy controls (<italic>P</italic>&#xA0;=&#xA0;0.45)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td valign="top">Agreement between QFT-IT &amp; TST results was poor in patients with IMID (agreement 70% <italic>k</italic>&#xA0;=&#xA0;0.37)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td valign="top">Agreement between QFT-IT &amp; TST results was good in healthy controls (<italic>n</italic>&#xA0;=&#xA0;93, agreement 83% <italic>k</italic>&#xA0;=&#xA0;0.64)</td>
          </tr>
